org.jetel.data

Class HashKey

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jetel.data.HashKey

  • public class HashKey
extends java.lang.Object
    Class associated with RecorKey and DataRecord Intended primarily to be used as a key for HashTable It only points to RecordKey and particular data record so we can perform hashing & lookup of the data record.
    Since:
    6. March 2004

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object object)
        Checks whether this HashKey equals to the given object. This happens only if the given object is also a HashKey, it has the same number of key fields and these are all equal. The RecordKey.compare(RecordKey, DataRecord, DataRecord) method is used for comparison of the key fields.
        Overrides:
        equals in class java.lang.Object
        Parameters:
        object - an object to be compared to this instance
        Returns:
        true if the given object is equal to this instance, false otherwise
        See Also:
        Object.equals(Object)
